.TH CLAUDESWITCH 1 "2026-03-18" "ClaudeSwitch" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
claudeswitch \- manage Claude Code API configuration profiles
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B claudeswitch
[\fIOPTION\fR]
.br
.B python3 -m claudeswitch
[\fIOPTION\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B claudeswitch
manages multiple Claude Code settings profiles stored under
.IR ~/.claude/ .
Each profile is a
.I settings\-<name>.json
file containing backend-specific environment variables.
Activating a profile copies it to
.I ~/.claude/settings.json
(the file Claude Code reads) and backs up the previous settings.
.PP
When invoked with no options,
.B claudeswitch
launches an interactive terminal UI (TUI) built with curses.
A graphical Qt UI is available via
.BR \-\-gui .
.PP
The project is distributed as a standard Python package and can be invoked
either through the installed
.B claudeswitch
console script or with
.BR "python3 -m claudeswitch" .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B init
Create
.IR ~/.claude/ ,
the backups directory, and a default
.I settings\-login.json
profile if they do not already exist.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-list
Print the names of all available profiles, marking the active one.
.TP
.BR \-s " \fIname\fR, " \-\-switch " \fIname\fR"
Switch to the named profile non-interactively.
Backs up the current
.I settings.json
before switching.
.TP
.B \-\-gui
Launch the graphical UI.
Requires
.B PySide6
or
.BR PyQt5 .
Falls back to the TUI if neither is installed.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Print a short usage summary and exit.
.SH TESTING
.nf
python3 -m pip install -e '.[test]'
pytest
coverage run --source=claudeswitch -m pytest tests/test_cli.py -q
coverage report -m
.fi
.PP
The automated tests cover the non-interactive CLI and data-layer behavior.
.SH TUI KEY BINDINGS
.SS Main menu
.TP
.BR "↑" " / " "↓"
Navigate the profile list.
.TP
.B Enter
Switch to the selected profile.
.TP
.B m
Open the More menu.
.TP
.B q
Quit.
.SS More menu
.TP
.B c
Configure the selected profile (edit API keys and URLs).
.TP
.B n
Create a new profile.
.TP
.B d
Delete the selected profile (confirmation required).
.TP
.B i
Initialise default profiles (creates
.I settings\-login.json
if absent).
.TP
.B <
Return to the main menu.
.SH PROFILE TYPES
Profile type is inferred from the profile name.
.TP
.B login
Uses an Anthropic subscription; no API key is required.
.TP
.B azure
Azure OpenAI backend.
Fields: Azure API Key, Endpoint URL, API Version, Deployment Name.
.TP
.B litellm
LiteLLM proxy backend.
Fields: API Key, Proxy URL (default
.IR http://localhost:4000 ).
.TP
.B asksage
AskSage backend.
Fields: API Key, Base URL, AskSage Token (optional).
.TP
.I anything else
Standard Anthropic API.
Fields: API Key, Base URL (default
.IR https://api.anthropic.com ).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.claude/settings.json
Active profile; read by Claude Code on every invocation.
.TP
.I ~/.claude/.claudeswitch
Plain-text file containing the name of the currently active profile.
.TP
.I ~/.claude/settings\-<name>.json
Stored profile file for profile
.IR name .
.TP
.I ~/.claude/backups/settings_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.json
Timestamped backups created automatically before each profile switch.
.SH INSTALLATION
.nf
git clone https://github.com/normanajn/ClaudeSwitch.git
cd ClaudeSwitch
python3 -m pip install .
python3 -m claudeswitch init
.fi
.PP
.B install.sh
runs
.B python3 -m pip install --user .[gui]
and then
.B python3 -m claudeswitch init
to create a default
.I login
profile.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
Python\ 3.9 or later.
.B PySide6
or
.B PyQt5
is required only for
.BR \-\-gui .
PyTest and Coverage are used for the automated test suite.
.SH EXAMPLES
List all profiles:
.PP
.nf
    claudeswitch \-\-list
.fi
.PP
Switch to the azure profile:
.PP
.nf
    claudeswitch \-\-switch azure
.fi
.PP
Launch the interactive TUI:
.PP
.nf
    claudeswitch
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR claude (1)
